-- NHL Ends Lockout, Schedules 720-Game Season to Begin Jan. 19
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-01-13T03:49:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-13/nhl-ends-lockout-schedules-720-game-season-to-begin-jan-19.html
The  National Hockey League  and the
players’ union today agreed to terms of a 10-year Collective
Bargaining Agreement to end the season’s lockout.  Training camps will open tomorrow with the 720-game regular-
season schedule to begin Jan. 19, the league said in a
statement. Each team will play 48 games.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  